@startuml fig-A04-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title ARP Spoofing — E2 PCAP Flow (Normal → Spoof → Detect → Mitigate)

participant "h1\n(victim)" as V #FFE0B2
participant "s1" as SW #BBDEFB
participant "h2\n(gateway)" as GW #C8E6C9
participant "h3\n(attacker)" as ATK #FFCDD2
participant "Detector\n(h4)" as DET #E1BEE7
participant "tcpdump" as CAP #ECEFF1

== PHASE 1 — NORMAL ARP (baseline) ==

V -> SW : ARP Request: who has 10.0.0.254?
SW -> GW : broadcast
GW -[#43A047]-> SW : ARP Reply: 10.0.0.254 is-at bb:bb
SW -[#43A047]-> V : forwarded reply
DET -> DET : learn: 10.0.0.254 → bb:bb
note right of CAP : R1: arp.opcode==1 >= 1\nR3: arp >= 10

== PHASE 2 — ARP SPOOFING ==

ATK -[#E53935]> SW : Gratuitous ARP: 10.0.0.254 is-at cc:cc
SW -[#E53935]> V : broadcast (victim updates cache)
note right of V #FFCDD2 : ARP cache poisoned:\n10.0.0.254 → cc:cc

DET -> DET : detect: 10.0.0.254 changed\nfrom bb:bb to cc:cc
DET -[#E53935]> DET : emit SPOOF alert\n(IP, old MAC, new MAC, timestamp)
note right of CAP : R2: arp.opcode==2 >= 5

V -> SW : ICMP to gateway (10.0.0.254)
SW -[#E53935]> ATK : traffic diverted to attacker
note right of ATK #FFCDD2 : MITM: packets transit\nthrough attacker

== PHASE 3 — MITIGATION ==

DET -[#1565C0]> SW : block MAC cc:cc\n(OVS rule or static ARP)
V -> SW : ICMP to gateway
SW -[#43A047]> GW : traffic restored to gateway
note right of GW #E8F5E9 : diversion stopped

legend right
  PCAP must show: normal ARP replies,
  gratuitous ARP from attacker and
  traffic restoration after mitigation.
  Alerts correlate with specific packets.
endlegend
@enduml
